latestPosts.caption:
I seldom make online declarations or tributes to people I love, but this deserves an exception. As far as I’m concerned, she is the true, living personification of the adage “woman of steel”. Strong, fierce and full of grit, yet equal parts poised, empathetic and vulnerable.

Mom, the way you’ve excelled at nurturing the family, managing work and still making time for self love leaves me in awe. You balance everything to perfection!

I’ve grown up watching you enjoy getting ready each morning- elegant and impeccable. Every time there’s a compliment coming my way, I cant help but relate - ‘I got it from my mama’. 

Thank God, I embody you - most of me reflects your personality and attributes - and I couldn’t be more grateful for that. (Well, some good genes are dad’s too, can’t deny!) But majorly, I am you. 

Happy Mother’s Day, Mom. We love you endlessly, beyond what words can express. You are our world and beyond and everything in between. ❤️ 

#happymothersday #weloveyoumom

latestPosts.caption:
1st day of one of the most fun trip we had in recent times (or do I say the same about them all ! 😀)

1. The mandatory picture outside the architectural marvel that is ‘Dubai Frame.’ Our first tourist spot of Day 1
2. A stunning view of this beautiful frame. It looks even more gorgeous with colourful beaming lights at night.
3. Me doing what I love to do the best.
4. The beautiful city from the top of Dubai Frame.
5. Mandatory pic outside the waterfront in Dubai Mall.
6. View of Dubai at nighttime from the top of Burj Khalifa. Honestly, the building is far more stunning from outside.
7. The ‘abra’ boats that float all across Dubai.
8. The iconic Dubai fountain outside the Mall; a sight to behold.
9. One of the best moments of the entire trip, when they played this song at Burj Khalifa. All heart ❤️ 

#dubaitrip #burjkhalifa #dubaimall #dubaitravel #dubaidowntown #dubaiframe

Oh Ladakh, you left us awed !
